Happy National Margarita Day! ğŸ¸ This Italian Margarita recipe with limoncello will transport you straight to the Amalfi coast! ğŸ‡®ğŸ‡¹ As the self-proclaimed margarita queen, itâ€™s no secret that I love dreaming up different margarita variations. Whether you celebrate this holiday with an Italian marg, a spicy marg, or an old faithful, I hope you enjoy it to the fullest (alongside some nachos, of course)! ğŸ¥‚

Ingredients:
1 ozÂ fresh lime juice
1 ozÂ freshÂ blood orange juice (or pomegranate juice if not in season)
1 ozÂ limoncello
2 ozÂ blanco tequila
Club soda, top top (optional)

Instructions:
1. Fill a cocktail shaker with ice and add in lime juice, blood orange juice, limoncello and tequila. Shake for 20-30 seconds or until the cocktail shaker is well chilled.Â 
2. Pour into a low glass with ice, top with club soda if desired and garnish with a blood orange slice.

Super Easy 4 Ingredient peanut butter cookies! ğŸª Crispy golden edges, gooey peanut butter centers. Bookmark these for your next sweet tooth!Â 

PEANUT BUTTER COOKIES:Â 
1 Â½ cups smooth peanut butterÂ 
1 Â½ cups brown sugarÂ 
2 large eggs, at room temp
1 Â½ tsp baking sodaÂ 
1 tsp vanilla paste, optionalÂ 

Instructions:Â 

1. Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line two medium rimmed baking sheets with parchment paper and set aside.Â 
2. In a bowl with a stand mixer or a medium bowl with a hand mixer add peanut butter and brown sugar. Mix together on medium-high for 2-3 minutes.Â 
3. Add eggs, baking soda and vanilla bean paste if using and mix together for another minute.Â 
4. With a 1 inch cookie scoop, scoop dough balls onto the baking sheet and create a criss cross pattern with a fork. Top with a little extra brown sugar if desired.Â 
5. Bake for 8-9 minutes or until the edges are slightly golden brown. Remove from the oven and leave on the baking sheet for an additional 3-5 minutes. Transfer to a wire baking rack to finish cooling.
